Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan tabled his Budget speech for the 2017/2018 financial year in Parliament on Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG - The Automobile Association of South Africa (AA) says an increase in fuel and Road Accident Fund levies is a blow to consumers.Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan tabled his Budget speech for the 2017/2018 financial year in Parliament yesterday. He announced that an additional 30 cents per litre will be added to the general fuel levy and nine cents a litre more to the Road Accident Fund.The AA'S Layton Beard says: South Africans already buckling will now have to dig even deeper in their pockets when many are questioning government spending. Beard adds they re concerned about the hike.